metadata.name: The Ocean of Clouds : Plane Spotting
metadata.description:
Water drop to the Ocean, 
Aeroplane to the Clouds  
The problems we have seem so big, 
Positive perspective is all that counts 

Captured at Brighton-Le-Sands Beach overlooking Sydney Airport in Australia.

This is a unique Cumulonimbus cloud formation observed while an aeroplane passes through the clouds. The image puts into perspective the huge disparity between human creation and nature creation with the flight looking like a small drop in the vast ocean of clouds.
